Steps to modify the original design to use an NTC thermistor:
1. Remove the LMT85
2. Solder silicon wires (which are temperature resistant) to a 10K 3950B NTC thermistor, for e.g: https://www.amazon.co.uk/gp/product/B07P5Q67RH
3. Attach the thermistor to the middle bottom of the heat plate with thermal paste, aluminium tape (optional) and kapton tape
4. Connect the 2 wires to TempData and GND on the TEMP pins
5. Connect a 1K resistor between VDD and TempData
6. Change the getTemp() function in the Arduino code as follows:
```
 // Thermistor parameters
 static const float beta = 3950.;
 static const float r_inf = 1.7632269789291097e-05; 
 static const float adc_max = 1023.;

 float getTemp(){
  float adc = 0;
  float r = 0;

  for (byte i = 0; i < 10; i++){ //Poll voltage reading 10 times
    adc = adc + analogRead(temp);
  }
  adc = adc / 10.;
  // Get thermistor current resistance
  r = adc / (adc_max - adc);
  // Convert resistance to degree C and return
  return beta / log(r / r_inf) - 273.15;
}
```

